ci: Add SHA matches in the cache and test stages.
- Introduce a step to get the short SHA of the current commit. - Include the short SHA in the cache tag used by the Build and push job. - Use the short SHA in the tag for testing the large-v3-zh docker image.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

ci: enhance CI security scans and artifact handling
- Update Trivy action used in vulnerability scans to 0.16.1 in both Python and UBI workflows - Ensure Trivy action always exits with code '1' on identified vulnerabilities in both Python and UBI workflows - Add `ignore-unfixed` flag to Trivy configuration to ignore unresolved vulnerabilities in both Python and UBI workflows - Bump `upload-artifact` action version to v4 and rename artifact for better differentiation in both Python and UBI workflows - Add conditional execution (`if: always()`) to ensure artifacts are always uploaded even if preceding steps fail - Introduce a new SARIF format Trivy vulnerability scan and upload the results to the GitHub Security tab for the UBI image - Modify the GitHub actions badge in the `README.md` to point to the Docker publish workflow instead of the scan workflow
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>
